SIMPLE: mailbox
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: mailbox
<hw>mail"box`</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A public box for
deposit of mail, where it is later picked up by the postal authority for
delivery.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> postbox, letter box.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A private box to recieve delivery of mail. The term
is used both for boxes receiving mail delivered by the public postal
authority, or by a private services, such as for mail to employees in
large corporations.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> letter box.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Computers)</fld> <def>A location within a computer
storage device where electronic mail is held until it is retrieved by
the addressee. Creation and use of an electronic <ex>mailbox</ex>
requires special software as well as a data storage device.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mail call</ent>⟦br⟧
